# ============================================================================
# _kontroll — zsh completion for **kontroll** — zsa/kontroll, the
#              official **Rust CLI for ZSA Technology Labs'
#              Keymapp API**.  Programmatically controls every ZSA
#              ergonomic keyboard — the **Moonlander Mark I**, the
#              **Voyager**, and the **ErgoDox EZ** — by speaking
#              gRPC over a local Unix-domain socket to the running
#              Keymapp daemon (the macOS/Linux/Windows Keymapp.app
#              that ZSA ships as the official user-side keyboard
#              configurator).  Lets shell scripts + window-manager
#              hooks + tmux session-start scripts dynamically:
#              connect to a specific keyboard, switch the active
#              layer (the multi-modal layer system at the heart of
#              every ZSA keyboard), set individual LED colors,
#              flash status LEDs, adjust per-key brightness, and
#              query connection status.  Rust=177 OPENING leg of
#              new Axis 122 (gRPC / Google RPC + Protocol Buffers
#              + HTTP/2 transport) via the canonical Rust gRPC
#              library **hyperium/tonic** (the de-facto Rust gRPC
#              dependency, by the Hyper / Tower / Tokio
#              maintainers).
# ============================================================================
#
