#
#   gRPC itself (Google Remote Procedure Call) is **the
#   universal high-performance RPC protocol** invented by
#   Google in 2015 (initially internal as Stubby, then open-
#   sourced as gRPC) and now a CNCF graduated project.
#   Architecture:
#
#     • **Wire format**:  Protocol Buffers (Google's binary
#       schema-driven serialization format, originally
#       designed in 2001 for Google's internal microservice
#       communication; now standardized as the universal RPC
#       message format for Kubernetes API objects,
#       Envoy/gRPC-Web, Apache Arrow Flight, every Google
#       Cloud API, every modern cloud-native control plane)
#     • **Transport**:  HTTP/2 (RFC 7540) — multiplexed
#       binary-framed streams over a single persistent TCP
#       connection with built-in flow control + header
#       compression (HPACK) + bidirectional streaming
#     • **Service definition**:  `.proto` schema files
#       defining typed RPC methods (Unary, Server-streaming,
#       Client-streaming, Bidirectional-streaming) with typed
#       request/response messages
#     • **Status codes**:  16 canonical gRPC status codes
#       (`OK`, `CANCELLED`, `UNKNOWN`, `INVALID_ARGUMENT`,
#       `DEADLINE_EXCEEDED`, `NOT_FOUND`, `ALREADY_EXISTS`,
#       `PERMISSION_DENIED`, `RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED`,
#       `FAILED_PRECONDITION`, `ABORTED`, `OUT_OF_RANGE`,
#       `UNIMPLEMENTED`, `INTERNAL`, `UNAVAILABLE`,
#       `DATA_LOSS`, `UNAUTHENTICATED`)
#     • **Authentication**:  Per-call metadata (HTTP/2
#       headers) — Authorization Bearer tokens, mTLS client
#       certs, Google ADC (Application Default Credentials),
#       AWS Signature V4
#     • **Load balancing**:  Round-robin, ringhash, weighted-
#       round-robin, locality-weighted via the xDS protocol
#       (Envoy's universal data-plane configuration API,
#       used by Linkerd / Istio / gRPC-Java / gRPC-Go / tonic)
#
#   gRPC is the protocol underlying:
